_pdbx_database_remark.id     700 
_pdbx_database_remark.text   
;SHEET
SHEET B1 OF THIS MOLECULE IS BIFURCATED.  IN ORDER TO
REPRESENT THIS FEATURE IN THE SHEET RECORDS BELOW,
TWO SHEETS *B1A* AND *B1B* ARE DEFINED.  STRANDS 5, 6, 7,
8, 9, AND 10 OF B1A ARE IDENTICAL TO STRANDS 2, 3, 4, 5, 6,
AND 7 OF B1B, RESPECTIVELY.
;
# 
_pdbx_entry_details.entry_id                 1BZM 
_pdbx_entry_details.compound_details         
;THE DRUG MOLECULE HAS WELL DEFINED ELECTRON DENSITY 
IN THE ACTIVE SITE OF THE ENZYME.  WHEN THE DRUG 
BINDS TO THE ENZYME, THE LOOP REGION COMPRISING OF 
RESIDUES LEU 198, THR 199 AND HIS 200 UNDERGOES A 
SIGNIFICANT CHANGE AS COMPARED TO THE NATIVE STRUCTURE.

ACTIVE SITE HYDROGEN BONDED SOLVENT NETWORK INVOLVING 
HIS 67 AND HIS 200 IS POSSIBLY IMPORTANT FOR THE 
CATALYTIC ACTIVITY AND INHIBITION OF THIS ISOENZYME.
;
_pdbx_entry_details.source_details           ? 
_pdbx_entry_details.nonpolymer_details       'ZINC ZN(II) IS THE CATALYTICALLY ESSENTIALL ZINC ION.' 
_pdbx_entry_details.sequence_details         ? 
_pdbx_entry_details.has_ligand_of_interest   ? 
